<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Grosvenor sale to UB
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Grosvenor Inns, through its Slug &amp; Lettuce subsidiary, has exchanged
contracts with Wiltshire Brewery, where UB Group has taken management
control, for the sale of its long freehold interest in The Water Rat, a
restaurant/cafe bar in Stratford-upon-Avon.
Consideration of Pounds 500,000 is to be satisfied by way of an allocation
of shares and a deferred consideration. The consideration is Pounds 100,000
by way of 1m new ordinaries in Wiltshire with no restrictions on disposal or
Pounds 200,000 by way of 7 per cent redeemable convertible loan note.
