<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Dickie reports sharp upturn to Pounds
298,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
James Dickie, a manufacturer of engineering components and assemblies, saw
pre-tax profits rise from Pounds 206,000 to Pounds 298,000 in the year to
August 31 following a sharp improvement in the second six months of the
year; the first six months saw a loss of Pounds 98,000.
Turnover fell from Pounds 26.5m to Pounds 15.4m following consolidation of
manufacturing activities, including the closure of Coalville Sheet Metal and
the sale of James Dickie Forgings to its management.
Earnings per share came through at 3.4p against 5.8p after tax of Pounds
89,000 (Pounds 152,000 credit). A single distribution of 1p (nil) is
proposed.
