<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Merchant Retail slides to Pounds 467,000
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MERCHANT RETAIL Group returned pre-tax profits of Pounds 467,000 for the
half year to September 26 on turnover of Pounds 88.8m.
Although the figures compared with Pounds 1.22m and Pounds 79m respectively
for the same period of the previous year directors said 'robust trading' was
experienced at its discount supermarkets and department stores.
Trading profits of the Normans supermarkets fell to Pounds 1.36m (Pounds 2m)
but at that level were considerably ahead of those for the second half of
the past year.
A slight decline in trading profits at the Joplings department stores to
Pounds 736,000 (Pounds 818,000) reflected tighter margins and an increase in
sales on interest-free credit.
The interim dividend is cut to 0.35p (1.1p), in line with the company's
objective of maintaining the full year pay-out - the final dividend was
omitted last time. Earnings on the enlarged capital emerged at 0.44p
(0.97p).
