<HEADLINE>
FT  11 NOV 92 / UK Company News: Dissidents fail at Hoskins
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP RAWSTORNE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An attempt by dissident shareholders to take over the management of Hoskins
Brewery, the Leicester-based brewer, collapsed yesterday.
Mr Richard Cattermole, chief executive of Ryan Elizabeth, an East Anglian
pubs and hotels company, and his associate, Mr Jeremy Lea, abandoned moves
to oust Messrs Barrie Hoar, chairman, and his brother Robert Hoar, from the
Hoskins board.
A statement said: 'Mr Cattermole believes the recent attention drawn to
Hoskins' financial performance will focus the minds of the Hoar brothers on
what has to be done to restore confidence.'
Mr Barrie Hoar welcomed the withdrawal, but said he was awaiting formal
confirmation.
