The hospital has grown up over the last 40 years and the intention is that
the present facilities should be rationalised and that a sound basis should
be provided for future development of the site.
The appointment will therefore involve major refurbishment of some of the
buildings, the building of extensions to others and the construction of new
facilities. Roads and car parking facilities on site will be upgraded and
extended.
The project will be divided into a number of phases, the second of which is
the construction of a new nucleus hospital. The whole development is
expected to be completed in July 1997 at a cost of Pounds 28m.
