</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Department of Trade and Industry has cleared the sale of part of
Cardwise, a credit card protection company owned by American Express, to
Credit Card Sentinel, the European arm of Datacard Corporation of
Minneapolis.
An inquiry into the sale was started by the Office of Fair Trading in June,
but the OFT recommended against referring the sale to the Monopolies and
Mergers Commission. Cardwise was formerly owned by the banks in the Access
consortium.
