<TEXT>
SAO PAULO fell 6.6 per cent yesterday as investors remained bearish about a
government tax reform proposal, which includes a controversial impost on
financial transactions, presented to Congress last week. At the closing bell
the Bovespa index of the 53 most-traded shares was down 2,846 points at
40,197.
