<HEADLINE>
FT  10 NOV 92 / Business and the Law: Fraud in firms - Legal Briefs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Touche has been offering advice on how to tackle the growing problem of
fraud by solicitors. Among its suggestions to the Law Society are: each firm
to maintain a specific level of partner's capital; compulsory review of a
firm's management systems before it is allowed to hold clients' money; and
partners to confirm compliance with accountants' reports rules.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 14
</PAGE>
